    <p class="text-gray-300">Definition 1 (Alternant code): A <span class="math">q</span>-ary alternant code of order <span class="math">r</span> associated to <span class="math">\\bm{x}=(x_{1},\\ldots,x_{n})\\in\\mathbb{F}_{q^{m}}^{n}</span> where all <span class="math">x_{i}</span>’s are distinct and <span class="math">\\bm{y}=(y_{1},\\ldots,y_{n})\\in\\left(\\mathbb{F}_{q^{m}}^{*}\\right)^{n}</span> denoted by <span class="math">\\mathscr{A}_{r}(\\bm{x},\\bm{y})</span> is</p>

