    <p class="text-gray-300">Let us assume that <span class="math">n=q^{m}</span>. When <span class="math">q</span> is fixed and <span class="math">m</span> tends to infinity then <span class="math">r_{\\text{crit}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{2\\,q^{m}\\log q}{m\\log m}}\\big{(}1+o(1)\\big{)}</span> and</p>

